      <li class="text-ink-200" aria-current="page">Best AI Tools for GEO</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="hero-fade relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container-wide grid gap-12 pt-12 pb-20 lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <span class="eyebrow">GEO Workflow Stack Guide</span>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          <span class="grad-text">Best AI Tools for GEO</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-300">
          The best AI tools for GEO are not a single platform — they are a stack assembled in the right sequence. This is the evergreen workflow guide: it organises every tool type by the specific job it does (audit, optimise, monitor, report), explains how to sequence your tool adoption as your programme matures, and shows you how to fill gaps without duplicating coverage. If you want a time-stamped view of what is new in 2026 specifically, see our <a href="/best-geo-tools-2026/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">2026 annual roundup</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Build Your GEO Stack</a>
