  <section id="faq" class="container-wide py-20">
    <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text sm:text-4xl">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-[var(--line)]">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What types of tools does a GEO programme actually need?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">A complete GEO programme requires tools across four jobs: audit (to establish a baseline and identify gaps), optimise (to improve content structure, semantic clarity, and entity signals), monitor (to track AI citation frequency over time and detect changes), and report (to communicate programme performance to stakeholders). Most teams start with a monitoring tool to establish baseline metrics, then add audit and optimisation tooling as the programme matures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can I use existing SEO tools for GEO, or do I need dedicated tools?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Some existing SEO tools are directly useful within a GEO workflow — particularly for technical audits, content quality analysis, structured data validation, and entity research. However, the core GEO measurement task (tracking brand citation frequency in AI-generated answers) requires dedicated tooling that existing SEO platforms were not designed to provide. The two categories are complementary: use SEO tools for the foundational work, dedicated GEO tools for AI-specific measurement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What should a GEO audit tool cover?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">A GEO audit should cover: current AI citation baseline; content structure analysis (whether your pages lead with bold declarative statements, use structured headers, and answer questions directly); structured data implementation; entity presence in knowledge graphs and authoritative third-party sources; and a competitive gap analysis showing which competitors are outperforming you in AI citations and why. No single tool covers all of these; a good audit combines a citation tracker, a content analyser, a schema validator, and an entity presence review.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does an optimisation tool for GEO actually do?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">GEO optimisation tools analyse existing content and recommend changes that increase its probability of being cited by AI models. Key functions include: identifying content that lacks a clear, quotable answer to the query it targets; recommending structural changes such as adding definition blocks, summary boxes, or FAQ sections; flagging structured data gaps or errors; and scoring content against criteria that GEO research has associated with higher citation rates, such as authoritative sourcing, specific factual claims, and clear entity references.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How do GEO reporting tools differ from standard analytics dashboards?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Standard analytics dashboards measure traffic, conversions, and traditional SEO performance. GEO reporting tools present AI-specific metrics: citation rate trends over time, share-of-voice versus named competitors, platform-by-platform visibility breakdown, and the correlation between optimisation activities and subsequent changes in citation frequency. Most GEO reporting is currently done by connecting monitoring platform data exports into existing BI tools such as Looker Studio or Power BI, rather than through a single dedicated GEO reporting platform.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

